The paper deals with the problem of extracting chemical structures from documents, which involves both image segmentation and structure prediction. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and deep learning (cs.DL). However, given that the paper focuses on using deep learning for both segmentation and prediction, cs.CV and cs.DL are the most likely sub-categories. The use of deep learning also suggests that the paper could be relevant to cs.CL, cs.LG, and cs.IR, as these sub-categories often involve the use of machine learning techniques.
